summary: BOTH POWER WINDOWS IN REAR OF CAR FAILED.    BOTH POWER WINDOWS FAILED EVEN THOUGH THEY HAVE RARELY BEEN USED.  DRIVER SIDE REAR WINDOW DROPS DOWN WHILE DRIVING CAUSING DISTRACTION TO DRIVER AND EXCESSIVE WIND AND WIND NOISE IN THE CAR.  A THIRD POWER WINDOW COMPONENT WAS REPLACED ON THE FRONT OF THE CAR WHILE STILL UNDER WARRANTY.      SUSPECT FAULTY WINDOW REGULATORS AS DEALER MENTIONED BOTH REGULATORS WOULD HAVE TO BE REPLACED.  DATE IS APPROXIMATE FOR 1ST WINDOW.  SECOND WINDOW FAILED ABOUT 7 MONTHS LATER.
